"use strict";(self.webpackChunk_hieudoanm_github_io_docs=self.webpackChunk_hieudoanm_github_io_docs||[]).push([["36607"],{77735(n){n.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"prompt-framework","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/prompt-framework","editUrl":"https://github.com/hieudoanm/hieudoanm/tree/master/packages/docs/docs/blog/2026-01-13-prompt-framework.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-01-13-prompt-framework.md","title":"Prompt Framework","description":"\u{1F4DA} Table of Contents","date":"2026-01-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Hello","permalink":"/blog/tags/hello","description":"Hello tag description"}],"readingTime":3.16,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Hieu Doan","title":"Software Engineer","url":"https://linkedin.com/in/hieudoanm","page":{"permalink":"/blog/authors/hieudoan"},"socials":{"x":"https://x.com/hieudoanm","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/hieudoanm/","github":"https://github.com/hieudoanm","newsletter":"https://hieudoanm.github.io"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/hieudoanm.png","key":"hieudoan"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"prompt-framework","title":"Prompt Framework","authors":"hieudoan","tags":["hello"]},"unlisted":false},"content":"## \u{1F4DA} Table of Contents\\n\\n- [\u{1F4DA} Table of Contents](#-table-of-contents)\\n- [\u{1F9E0}\u2728 Introduction](#-introduction)\\n- [\u{1F9E9} 5W1H](#-5w1h)\\n  - [\u{1F464} **Who**](#-who)\\n  - [\u{1F4CC} **What**](#-what)\\n  - [\u{1F3AF} **Why**](#-why)\\n  - [\u23F1\uFE0F **When** _(optional)_](#\uFE0F-when-optional)\\n  - [\u{1F30D} **Where** _(optional)_](#-where-optional)\\n  - [\u2699\uFE0F **How**](#\uFE0F-how)\\n- [\u2705 Good Prompt vs \u274C Bad Prompt](#-good-prompt-vs--bad-prompt)\\n  - [\u274C Bad Prompt](#-bad-prompt)\\n  - [\u2705 Good Prompt](#-good-prompt)\\n- [\u{1F517} Combination](#-combination)\\n  - [\u{1F9E0} Prompt Formula](#-prompt-formula)\\n  - [\u{1F501} Reusable Prompt Template](#-reusable-prompt-template)\\n  - [4\uFE0F\u20E3 Why This Works](#4\uFE0F\u20E3-why-this-works)\\n- [Final Thoughts \u{1F680}](#final-thoughts-)\\n\\n## \u{1F9E0}\u2728 Introduction\\n\\n\u{1F9E0} Prompting is quickly becoming a **core skill** for developers, designers, and knowledge workers.\\n\\n\u23F3 A good prompt can save hours of work, while a vague one can lead to confusing or unusable results.\\n\\n\u{1F9E9} Think of prompts as **interfaces for thinking** \u2014 the clearer your interface, the better the output.\\n\\n\u{1F680} This post introduces a **simple, reusable Prompt Framework** that helps you to:\\n\\n- \u{1F5E3}\uFE0F communicate intent clearly\\n- \u{1F3AF} get more consistent results\\n- \u{1F501} reuse prompts across tools and projects\\n\\n---\\n\\ntruncate\\n\\n## \u{1F9E9} 5W1H\\n\\n\u{1F9E0} One of the easiest ways to structure a strong prompt is by borrowing the classic **5W1H framework**.\\n\\n### \u{1F464} **Who**\\n\\n\u{1F464} Who is the AI supposed to be?\\n\\n- A senior engineer\\n- A product manager\\n- A teacher explaining to beginners\\n\\n> _\u201CAct as a senior backend engineer\u2026\u201D_\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \u{1F4CC} **What**\\n\\n\u{1F4CC} What exactly do you want?\\n\\n- Generate code\\n- Review text\\n- Explain a concept\\n\\n> _\u201CExplain how Kafka consumer groups work\u2026\u201D_\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \u{1F3AF} **Why**\\n\\n\u{1F3AF} Why are you asking?\\n\\n- Learning\\n- Production use\\n- Decision making\\n\\n\u{1F9E0} This helps the model choose the **right depth and tone**.\\n\\n> _\u201C\u2026so I can explain it to junior developers.\u201D_\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \u23F1\uFE0F **When** _(optional)_\\n\\n\u23F1\uFE0F When are time or context constraints relevant?\\n\\n- Current trends\\n- Backward compatibility\\n- Version-specific behavior\\n\\n> _\u201CUsing Kafka 3.x\u2026\u201D_\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \u{1F30D} **Where** _(optional)_\\n\\n\u{1F30D} Where will this be used?\\n\\n- Web\\n- Mobile\\n- Backend\\n- React, Spring Boot, FastAPI\\n\\n> _\u201C\u2026in a Spring Boot application.\u201D_\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \u2699\uFE0F **How**\\n\\n\u2699\uFE0F How should the output look?\\n\\n- Bullet points\\n- Code only\\n- Step-by-step explanation\\n\\n> _\u201CUse simple examples and diagrams in text.\u201D_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \u2705 Good Prompt vs \u274C Bad Prompt\\n\\n### \u274C Bad Prompt\\n\\n> \u201CExplain Kafka\u201D\\n\\n\u{1F6A8} Problems:\\n\\n- \u{1F464} No role\\n- \u{1F3AF} No goal\\n- \u{1F30D} No context\\n- \u2699\uFE0F No format\\n- \u274C No example\\n\\n\u{1F914} The AI must **guess everything**, which often leads to generic or unfocused answers.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \u2705 Good Prompt\\n\\n> \u201CAct as a senior backend engineer.  \\n> Explain Kafka consumer groups in simple terms for junior developers, using Kafka 3.x and a Spring Boot context.  \\n> Use bullet points and a short example, similar to explaining how HTTP load balancing works.\u201D\\n\\n\u2705 Why this works:\\n\\n- \u{1F464} Clear role\\n- \u{1F3AF} Clear goal\\n- \u{1F30D} Clear context\\n- \u{1F4D0} Clear format\\n- \u{1F9E9} Clear example\\n\\n\u{1F9E0} Examples act as **anchors** \u2014 they show the AI _what \u201Cgood\u201D looks like_, not just what to do.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \u{1F517} Combination\\n\\n\u{1F517} The real power comes from **combining frameworks**.\\n\\n### \u{1F9E0} Prompt Formula\\n\\n```text\\nRole + Task + Context + Constraints + Output Format + (Optional) Example\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \u{1F501} Reusable Prompt Template\\n\\n```text\\nAct as [ROLE].\\n\\nYour task is to [WHAT].\\nThis is for [WHY].\\nContext: [WHERE / WHEN].\\n\\nOutput requirements:\\n\\n- Format: [FORMAT]\\n- Style: [STYLE]\\n- Length: [LENGTH]\\n- Example (optional): [REFERENCE OR SAMPLE]\\n```\\n\\n\u{1F501} You can store these templates and reuse them across:\\n\\n- ChatGPT\\n- Claude\\n- GitHub Copilot\\n- Internal AI tools\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4\uFE0F\u20E3 Why This Works\\n\\n\u{1F9E0} This framework works because it **separates structure from intent**.\\n\\n- \u{1F9E9} **Who + How \u2192 quality control (template-owned)**  \\n  \u{1F39B}\uFE0F These define _how_ the AI should think and respond.  \\n  \u{1F4C8} They improve output quality regardless of topic.\\n\\n- \u{1F3AF} **What + Why \u2192 intent (user-owned)**  \\n  \u{1F9E0} These define _what matters_.  \\n  \u{1F64B} Only the user knows the real task and success criteria.\\n\\n- \u{1F30D} **Where / When \u2192 relevance (user-owned, optional)**  \\n  \u{1F9ED} These ground the response in a real-world context, when needed.\\n\\n\u{1F9E9} Examples sit at the boundary:\\n\\n- Optional\\n- User-provided\\n- Extremely powerful when clarity or style matters\\n\\n\u2696\uFE0F By keeping:\\n\\n- \u{1F3D7}\uFE0F structure in the **template**\\n- \u270D\uFE0F meaning in the **user\u2019s hands**\\n\\n\u{1F680} you avoid over-constraining prompts while still getting **consistent, high-quality results**.\\n\\n> \u2728 **Template sets clarity. User sets purpose. Examples set direction.**\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Final Thoughts \u{1F680}\\n\\n\u{1F9E0} Prompting is not about \u201Ctalking nicely to AI\u201D.  \\n\u{1F3AF} It\u2019s about **thinking clearly and expressing intent**.\\n\\n\u2705 A good prompt:\\n\\n- \u2744\uFE0F reduces ambiguity\\n- \u{1F4C8} improves output quality\\n- \u23F3 saves time\\n\\n\u{1F680} Start simple. Use 5W1H.  \\n\u{1F501} Then combine and refine as you go.\\n\\n> \u2728 **Clear thinking \u2192 Clear prompts \u2192 Better results**\\n\\n\u{1F604} Happy prompting!"}]}}')}}]);